problem:
In the diagram, square $ABCD$ has sides of length 4, and $\triangle ABE$ is equilateral. Line segments $BE$ and $AC$ intersect at $P$. Point $Q$ is on $BC$ so that $PQ$ is perpendicular  to $BC$ and $PQ=x$. [asy]
pair A, B, C, D, E, P, Q;
A=(0,0);
B=(4,0);
C=(4,-4);
D=(0,-4);
E=(2,-3.464);
P=(2.535,-2.535);
Q=(4,-2.535);
draw(A--B--C--D--A--E--B);
draw(A--C);
draw(P--Q, dashed);
label("$A$", A, NW);
label("$B$", B, NE);
label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$D$", D, SW);
label("$E$", E, S);
label("$P$", P, W);
label("$Q$", Q, dir(0));
label("$x$", (P+Q)/2, N);
label("4", (A+B)/2, N);
[/asy]

Find the value of $x$ in simplest radical form.

